				<td colspan="2"><span>This was for new issues.  I hadnt completely read the sumamry, I was just copying and pasting to make sure it got up.  When I read it later, I noticed that.
<br />

<br />
From this thread:<a target="_new" href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=bardbalance&amp;message.id=913&amp;jump=true">http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=bardbalance&amp;message.id=913&amp;jump=true</a>
<br />

<br />

<br />
5. Better Mitigation 
<br />
Currently being evaluated, this will most likely be considered as part of the class Re-Envision process.
<br />
Bards have the worst melee avoidance/mitigation even though bards are a plate class.  This may be a result of our AC/avoidance softcap set too low or simply becuase our riposte, parry &amp; dodge base skills are too low.  Many feel that silk casters can out survive bards when they are being attacked.
<br />
Itemization (bard armor) has an AC that is also too low.</span></td>
