				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Bard Top 10 Issue Search, Take 2, Voting<a name="74581"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 17 05 3:41 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>There's already a DPS issue on the list, crowding it with another one would be a waste.  Quoted from the above link:  &quot;1. Raise Melee DPS back to 65% of a warrior Currently being evaluated - DPS for all classes to be evaluated with the class Re-Envision process
<br />

<br />
Equally equiped bards (AA, attack, haste, items, weapons) do around 50% of warrior damage when they are attacking from behind and warriors are attacking from the front.  This is below what bards should do.
<br />

<br />
This problem hits hard especially on raids.  After the first couple of any class, the remaining aspects players can add is DPS or healing.  Since bards have such little DPS, after the first two, additional bards desirability in raids falls very low.
<br />

<br />
The fact is, every other class can out DPS a bard (though it makes sense for some to perform their primary function such as healing).  Why is a mostly melee hybrid the worst DPS class in EQ?
<br />
As a hybrid, bards shouldn't be the worst at offense and defense.  Every other melee/hybrid class excells in one of those categories.&quot;
<br />

<br />
However, if you think the wording on it needs to be changed, we can deal with that.  
<br />

<br />

<br />
Also, I have to remove the epic 1.5 votes.  Thats also up on our top 10 and I will be re-wording these 2 issues and I'll let you guys add your thoughts before I change them.
<br />

<br />
EDIT:  Now that I think about it, I'm probably going to leave the DPS part as is, at least until a bit after the first re-envisioning patch.  With luck we'll hear something shortly after that about what they plan to do DPS wise.  At least thats what Brenlo has hinted at.  If you guys really want it changed say so and I'll do it, tho.</span></td>
