				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">With double attack, we would well surpass the 65% of warrior damage we want and alot of jealous classes would complain and they would just remove it again. 
<br />
</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
How do you know?  and So what if we surpass 65% of warrior damage?  that metric was offered up by the devs during Kunark what makes anyone think its valid now?
<br />

<br />
(repost from something i said on TCH):
<br />

<br />
Giving bards the Double Attack Skill has many benefits:
<br />

<br />
*Easy for devs to implement - its as close to copy and paste code as you can get
<br />
*It does not require the evaluation of events, encounters or itemization to be implemented - tweaking these things based on the needs of one class can have a variety of unintended consequences
<br />
*It scales - this change would affect positively bards of every level, casual vs raider, level of progression
<br />
*It is easy to manipulate - in the event its not enough, its simple to add a higher cap to DA for bards
<br />
*It uses the oldest existing components of game mechanics - its a basic skill that has been in place since the advent of the game. Its tried and true.
<br />
*It is low controversy - this is certainly up for debate, but I believe most classes don't even know we don't have this skill already.
<br />
*Its highly visable - you can see the skill in your skill list and see the message as it raises each level.
<br />
</span></td>
